<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Cardiac Pacemaker Safety & Evolution</h1>
    <p>Electrical Safety Testing and Design Considerations</p>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>This project investigates the evolution of pacemakers from basic analog pulse generators to advanced programmable devices. It emphasizes the importance of safety in biomedical devices, with a specific focus on pacemakers that operate directly with heart tissue.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Objectives</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Understand the historical and technological evolution of cardiac pacemakers.</li>
        <li>Analyze the design criteria from a biomedical engineering perspective.</li>
        <li>Perform safety testing procedures for electrical parameters in implantable devices.</li>
        <li>Evaluate validation and regulatory testing standards (e.g., ISO, IEC).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Topics Covered</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Types of pacemakers and their mechanisms</li>
        <li>Electrical stimulation principles</li>
        <li>Testing and validation of pacing circuits</li>
        <li>Failure modes and patient safety protocols</li>
        <li>Ethical and regulatory standards in device approval</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Developed a simulation model for cardiac pulse delivery</li>
        <li>Tested electrode materials and insulation quality</li>
        <li>Proposed a risk mitigation protocol for current leakage</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
